tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, total cholesterol, and creatinine, with low total bilirubin and mildly elevated chloride. These findings suggest suboptimal glycemic control, significant hypercholesterolemia, and possible renal impairment. Other parameters, including liver enzymes and electrolytes, are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk are recommended.
